[Close to You]

70
00:06:07,580 --> 00:06:09,770
[EP. 27: Once I Wished for "Us," Now I Wish
for "You and Me"]

71
00:06:11,270 --> 00:06:14,200
We'll wash some more vegetables.
You guys eat first.

72
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,790
Why are Captain and Yu Mingxi taking so long?

73
00:06:16,790 --> 00:06:17,830
I'm starving.

74
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:19,680
They're in the honeymoon phase.

75
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,410
Can't get enough of each other.

76
00:06:22,830 --> 00:06:25,030
Aren't those two in the honeymoon phase?

77
00:06:25,030 --> 00:06:25,710
Sorry,

78
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:28,220
the food in front of me is more important now.

79
00:06:31,470 --> 00:06:32,530
Yours tastes better than mine.

80
00:06:32,530 --> 00:06:33,000
Really?

81
00:06:33,800 --> 00:06:34,670
Do you want this?

82
00:06:34,670 --> 00:06:35,000
Yes.

83
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,159
How did Captain and Yu Mingxi get together?

84
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:40,630
Was it because of that love letter?

85
00:06:40,630 --> 00:06:41,690
Well, in that case,

86
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:43,650
I was their number one wingman.

87
00:06:44,600 --> 00:06:45,680
Well, in that case,

88
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:48,720
you also wrote a love letter to Jiang Bohan?

89
00:06:50,350 --> 00:06:51,680
That's all in the past.

90
00:06:53,070 --> 00:06:54,070
That's not right.

91
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:56,280
I think it was earlier than the love letter.

92
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:57,340
Earlier than that?

93
00:06:57,600 --> 00:06:58,720
Then when was it?

94
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:01,240
They first met at a barbershop.

95
00:07:01,260 --> 00:07:03,320
It must have been love at first sight.

96
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:05,360
How about...

97
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,390
we make a bet?

98
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:10,000
Bet on what?

99
00:07:11,190 --> 00:07:11,950
On...

100
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:13,480
Whoever loses has to

101
00:07:14,070 --> 00:07:15,330
drink this pot of soup.

102
00:07:15,630 --> 00:07:16,000
Deal.

103
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,950
You're definitely gonna lose.

104
00:07:17,950 --> 00:07:19,120
If you don't believe me, ask You Jingchu.

105
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,510
He's basically her brother.

106
00:07:20,510 --> 00:07:21,120
He must know

107
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:23,120
when Yu Mingxi started liking Captain.

108
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,250
Right, You Jingchu?

109
00:07:27,430 --> 00:07:28,360
Yu Mingxi...

110
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:30,890
doesn't like Jiang Bohan.

111
00:07:31,830 --> 00:07:32,270
Drink.

112
00:07:33,560 --> 00:07:34,760
You won't say it, huh?

113
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:36,870
Be careful.

114
00:07:38,070 --> 00:07:39,270
There are three of us.

115
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,760
She doesn't like him?

116
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,070
If she doesn't like him, then what are they doing...

117
00:07:42,070 --> 00:07:43,600
What are you talking about?

118
00:07:43,870 --> 00:07:45,120
Mingxi, you're finally here.

119
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:46,159
I'm famished.

120
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:46,960
Let's eat.

121
00:07:48,480 --> 00:07:49,010
Captain.

122
00:07:49,270 --> 00:07:50,680
Just two types of vegetables.

123
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,040
What took you so long to wash them?

124
00:07:52,040 --> 00:07:56,600
-So long.
-So long.

125
00:07:58,190 --> 00:07:58,510
Captain,

126
00:07:58,510 --> 00:07:59,720
we've just made a bet.

127
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:02,610
Was it love at first sight for you with Yu Mingxi?

128
00:08:03,430 --> 00:08:04,490
Let's all eat, eat.

129
00:08:04,870 --> 00:08:05,800
Stop gossiping.

130
00:08:06,440 --> 00:08:07,640
Embarrassed, are we?

131
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:10,280
Come on, cheers.

132
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,040
A small victory!

133
00:08:11,040 --> 00:08:11,480
Raise our cups.

134
00:08:11,480 --> 00:08:12,190
Cheers!

135
00:08:16,280 --> 00:08:17,280
Jie,

136
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:20,000
that's kinda lame of you.

137
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,260
Drinking orange juice again?

138
00:08:23,720 --> 00:08:24,980
You're still the best.

139
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,580
Our group is about to break up!

140
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:30,560
You're not getting any younger.

141
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:33,620
Shouldn't you hurry up and find yourself a girlfriend?

142
00:08:35,030 --> 00:08:36,049
If I'm in a relationship,

143
00:08:36,049 --> 00:08:37,020
what about Yang?

144
00:08:37,669 --> 00:08:39,000
You can't pin this on me.

145
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,100
I already have someone I like.

146
00:08:41,120 --> 00:08:44,510
-Oh.
-Oh.

147
00:08:45,370 --> 00:08:47,860
All of you are taken now.

148
00:08:48,630 --> 00:08:50,230
What about you, You Jingchu?

149
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:51,240
Shut up.

150
00:08:51,620 --> 00:08:53,020
Okay, now I can rest easy.

151
00:08:54,830 --> 00:08:56,290
When are you guys leaving?

152
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:59,200
I'm waiting for Yu Mingxi's offer.

153
00:08:59,950 --> 00:09:01,550
What major did Yu Mingxi apply for?

154
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:03,060
She applied for Sports Management.

155
00:09:03,060 --> 00:09:05,860
UCLA's Sports Management program is very famous.

156
00:09:06,650 --> 00:09:08,380
How's your application going?

157
00:09:08,550 --> 00:09:11,150
Have you submitted your language test scores?

158
00:09:13,060 --> 00:09:13,750
I...

159
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,430
It's a day of celebration.

160
00:09:16,430 --> 00:09:18,510
Why are you putting pressure on our Corn?

161
00:09:18,510 --> 00:09:19,710
Reflect on yourself.

162
00:09:19,790 --> 00:09:21,090
What's with this "you" and "our" talk?

163
00:09:21,090 --> 00:09:21,800
No manners.

164
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:27,490
Captain.

165
00:09:28,550 --> 00:09:29,610
I'll miss you guys.

166
00:09:30,270 --> 00:09:32,150
If I still can't find a girlfriend by then,

167
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:33,220
I'll come pester you.

168
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:34,840
Don't find me annoying when that happens.

169
00:09:34,840 --> 00:09:35,170
Okay.

170
00:09:35,240 --> 00:09:35,700
Come on.

171
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,460
Cheers.

172
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:44,440
It's rare that we're all together like this.

173
00:09:44,440 --> 00:09:45,790
Let's take a group photo.

174
00:09:45,790 --> 00:09:46,660
-Sure.
-Sure.

175
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:49,550
I'll be in the front so that your face looks smaller.

176
00:09:49,550 --> 00:09:50,290
Everyone's in the frame.

177
00:09:50,290 --> 00:09:50,680
Okay.

178
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:51,550
Ready.

179
00:09:51,950 --> 00:09:53,590
Three, two, one.

180
00:09:59,770 --> 00:10:01,430
I've had the lawyer review the contract.

181
00:10:01,430 --> 00:10:02,960
Everything looks good now.

182
00:10:03,030 --> 00:10:04,830
But you need to think it through.

183
00:10:05,050 --> 00:10:06,850
This is a four-year commitment.

184
00:10:07,210 --> 00:10:09,300
Once you sign, there's no backing out.

185
00:10:09,300 --> 00:10:10,420
If you breach the contract,

186
00:10:10,420 --> 00:10:13,680
the team won't be able to compromise
on the penalty clause.

187
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,590
The team's been pushing so hard.

188
00:10:25,680 --> 00:10:27,480
I need to notify them right away.

189
00:10:38,530 --> 00:10:39,240
I signed it.

190
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,120
That's great.

191
00:10:42,450 --> 00:10:43,510
Congratulations!

192
00:10:46,840 --> 00:10:48,970
I'll take you to meet someone tonight.

193
00:10:50,360 --> 00:10:51,840
Who is it? So mysterious.

194
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:53,750
You'll see when we get there.

195
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:55,480
It's someone who's very important to me.

196
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:55,970
Okay.

197
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:57,750
I still have an hour before I get off work.

198
00:10:57,750 --> 00:10:58,950
I'll come pick you up.

199
00:11:08,580 --> 00:11:10,910
How's it going? Did you sign the contract?

200
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:12,210
Just signed it.

201
00:11:13,960 --> 00:11:14,670
What are you doing?

202
00:11:14,670 --> 00:11:16,270
Why is it so noisy over there?

203
00:11:16,600 --> 00:11:19,120
Today's the last round of UCLA's admission interviews.

204
00:11:19,120 --> 00:11:20,080
I've come to help.

205
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,010
We need to meet all the applicants.

206
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,770
Wait, what did you just say?

207
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:30,300
I said I'm doing interviews.

208
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,440
There's half an hour left.

209
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:32,910
I'll come find you when it's over.

210
00:11:32,910 --> 00:11:33,570
I have to go.

211
00:11:33,630 --> 00:11:34,020
I'm hanging up.

212
00:11:34,020 --> 00:11:34,560
Bye-bye.

213
00:12:01,170 --> 00:12:02,320
I'm at work right now.

214
00:12:02,320 --> 00:12:03,550
It's not convenient to take calls.

215
00:12:03,550 --> 00:12:04,350
What's wrong?

216
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:07,660
What time did your shift start today?

217
00:12:08,030 --> 00:12:08,910
I'm on the early shift today.

218
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:10,510
Of course, it started at 8 AM.

219
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,570
Didn't you go to the interview?

220
00:12:13,790 --> 00:12:15,120
Wait for me at the store.

221
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,410
I'm coming over now.

222
00:12:20,890 --> 00:12:23,090
Why does Jiang Bohan sound a little off?

223
00:12:24,020 --> 00:12:24,850
Oh no,

224
00:12:25,040 --> 00:12:27,100
he couldn't have found out, could he?

225
00:12:38,210 --> 00:12:39,480
Did you know all along

226
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:41,910
that Yu Mingxi didn't apply to UCLA?

227
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:50,000
Where are you going?

228
00:12:50,130 --> 00:12:54,190
Today is Boyang's death anniversary.
We have to go visit his grave later.

229
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:56,910
What's the matter, Corn?

230
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,060
Why are we running?

231
00:13:04,510 --> 00:13:05,440
What's going on?

232
00:13:14,390 --> 00:13:15,150
Yu Mingxi!

233
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:18,320
Yu Mingxi!

234
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:19,050
Jiang Bohan!

235
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:21,240
Yu Mingxi!

236
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,320
Explain yourself!

237
00:13:49,140 --> 00:13:50,800
What's wrong with you two now?

238
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,180
Don't ask anymore.

239
00:13:53,790 --> 00:13:55,480
Why can't you just talk to him?

240
00:13:56,750 --> 00:13:58,910
You can't keep hiding from him forever, right?

241
00:13:58,910 --> 00:14:00,100
I lied to him.

242
00:14:02,250 --> 00:14:03,560
He won't forgive me.

243
00:14:12,530 --> 00:14:13,480
Yu Mingxi!

244
00:14:14,330 --> 00:14:15,330
Yu Mingxi.

245
00:14:17,820 --> 00:14:18,480
If you don't go,

246
00:14:18,480 --> 00:14:19,740
then I won't go either.

247
00:14:21,120 --> 00:14:21,790
Yu Mingxi.

248
00:14:24,120 --> 00:14:25,380
I know you're in there.

249
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:28,940
I'll wait for you outside.

250
00:14:30,820 --> 00:14:32,420
I'll wait until you come out.

251
00:15:09,550 --> 00:15:10,610
It's already late.

252
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:13,320
Why don't you go outside and talk to him?

253
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:16,800
He's stubborn as hell.

254
00:15:17,550 --> 00:15:18,670
If you don't go out,

255
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:21,370
he definitely won't leave.

256
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:55,460
Corn is not coming out.

257
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:57,800
You should go.

258
00:16:00,000 --> 00:16:00,550
Go back.

259
00:16:01,530 --> 00:16:02,170
It's so late.

260
00:16:02,170 --> 00:16:02,840
Go home.

261
00:16:08,390 --> 00:16:10,720
Since when can you make decisions for her?

262
00:16:14,790 --> 00:16:17,120
I don't think I made myself clear just now.

263
00:16:17,870 --> 00:16:18,790
What I mean is,

264
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,360
stop bothering her.

265
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:22,510
Get lost.

266
00:16:28,150 --> 00:16:28,750
Do it.

267
00:16:30,320 --> 00:16:31,320
If hitting me

268
00:16:32,120 --> 00:16:33,850
will make you stop blaming her,

269
00:16:34,670 --> 00:16:36,200
then go ahead and continue.

270
00:16:56,750 --> 00:16:57,790
I promised my dad

271
00:16:58,320 --> 00:16:59,850
I'd go out and see the world.

272
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:01,850
Jiang Bohan,

273
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:03,700
let's go abroad together.

274
00:17:05,680 --> 00:17:07,480
Then, let's work hard together.

275
00:17:12,290 --> 00:17:14,020
How's your application going?

276
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,000
Have you submitted your language test scores?

277
00:17:29,400 --> 00:17:31,880
I've... never been good at pretending.

278
00:17:32,120 --> 00:17:34,720
The look of love in one's eyes cannot be hidden.

279
00:17:44,350 --> 00:17:45,570
Just make a wish.

280
00:17:47,310 --> 00:17:47,840
Alright.

281
00:17:48,180 --> 00:17:50,380
Then I'll share half of my wish with you.

282
00:17:50,800 --> 00:17:51,320
Really?

283
00:17:52,790 --> 00:17:54,070
